<br>
You could start as like 8 classes, but only one was a hero (pally) and you had to achieve a book to become a sage (basicly a slightly less accomplished hero)<br>
<br>
You could change your class as many times as you wanted so long as the character was lvl 35+ And when you changed your class you lost a few of your HP/MANA based on what you previously were. You had to get 35 again to change though.<br>
<br>
If you were to implement something like this in EQ, it would HAVE to require the player to hit 60, Class title and blow another 20-30aaxp for the option, choose your new class then DING 61 (basicly) and become LVL 1 in the new class without any abilities from the old class until you hit 10 (or you regain your old abilities as you level). Otherwise you'd see lvl 50 EVERYTHING's running around soloing VS/Trak/Etc.<br>
<br>
